cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper discusses a method for estimating the relative z-position of each individual section in a section series, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.NE) applications such as volumetric anatomy reconstruction. The use of Open Source plugins for TrakEM2 and ImageJ also suggests a focus on software development and implementation, which could fall under categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of microscopy data and image processing techniques could also relate to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
